This paper is about improving the efficiency and quality of neural data-to-text generation using a plan-based approach. The paper focuses on introducing new components to the existing framework to improve the generation process. The paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which is associated with the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques to improve the efficiency of the generation process, which is associated with the cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of reranking and referring expression generation techniques, which are associated with the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
